brazen temperament, and is often spotted leading shoals around the shallows near the For'ard Cabins with a self-assured grace. Guests have likened its presence to that of a conscientious, well-versed caretaker."],"Item":["0","47988"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","730"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingSpot":["0","295"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1438":{"Text":["","As pleated matamata age, their shells continue to grow indefinitely. According to legend, the largest and most ancient specimens eventually fuse with the landscape, blocking rivers in the process\u2500the once mighty roar of water reduced to a mere muttering. Though naturalists have yet to observe the phenomena in the wild, this specimen renders the tales believable."],"Item":["0","47989"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","730"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","300"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1439":{"Text":["","Capable of singlehandedly reducing the largest of predators to naught but a pile of polished bones, this wavekin combines the voraciousness of its kin with an independent tenacity that is chilling to behold."],"Item":["0","47990"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","730"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","2"],"FishingSpot":["0","302"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["False","True"],"AchievementCredit":["0","1145"]},"1440":{"Text":["","The rhomboid form of this pale yellow fish closely resembles fallen foliage. Indeed, local folklore tells of leaves borne on the wind morphing into wavekin after alighting on the surface of the Iq Br'aax reservoir."],"Item":["0","47991"],"GatheringItemLevel":["0","730"],"":["0","7000"],"IsHidden":["False","True"],"FishingRecordType":["0","3"],"FishingSpot":["0","309"],"GatheringSubCategory":["0","2515"],"IsInLog":["Fal